article.description: Trey Freeman scored six of his career-high 38 points in overtime to give Old Dominion a 74-69 victory over Charlotte on Saturday night.
article.headline: Freeman has 38, Old Dominion tops Charlotte 74-69 in OT
article.linkText: Freeman has 38, Old Dominion tops Charlotte 74-69 in OT
article.story: CHARLOTTE, N.C. -- Trey Freeman scored six of his career-high 38 points in overtime to give Old Dominion a 74-69 victory over Charlotte on Saturday night. Freeman forced the overtime with a 3-pointer with 18 seconds left in regulation and got his career high on a jumper that made it a two-possession game with 17 seconds left in OT. Freeman had four quick points in overtime as Charlotte didn't score until Braxton Ogbueze's layup with 1:08 left. Aaron Bacote had two free throws for the Monarchs at 56 seconds but Joseph Uchebo quickly got that back with a layup at 45 seconds before Freeman's last bucket. Charlotte missed a 3 and Jordan Baker hit one last free throw. Brandan Stith added 14 points for Old Dominion (13-10, 6-4 Conference USA). Uchebo had 18 points and 19 rebounds for the 49ers (8-15, 4-6). Ogbueze, Jon Davis and Curran Scott had 15 points each.
